{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' __issue_context__.json\"","aggregated_output":"{\n  \"body\": \"There is currently this tree:\\n\\n```\\ndiamine oxidase activity [EC:1.4.3.22 {source=\\\"skos:broadMatch\\\"}]\\n   |__histamine oxidase activity [EC:1.4.3.22 {source=\\\"skos:broadMatch\\\"}]\\n   |__putrescine oxidase activity [EC:1.4.3.10 {source=\\\"skos:exactMatch\\\"}]\\n   |__protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity [EC:1.4.3.13 {source=\\\"skos:exactMatch\\\"}]\\n```\\n\\nEC:1.4.3.22 is:\\nReaction catalysed: histamine + O2 + H2O = imidazole-4-acetaldehyde + H2O2 + NH4(+)\\nComments: A group of enzymes that oxidize diamines, such as histamine, and also some primary monoamines but have little or no activity toward secondary and tertiary amines.\\n\\nAlso, protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity is not a 'diamine oxidase activity'.\\n\\nSo:\\n- [x] Remove  EC:1.4.3.22 {source=\\\"skos:broadMatch\\\"} from 'histamine oxidase activity' and leave as broadMatch on parent 'diamine oxidase activity'\\n- [x] change parent of protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity to 'GO:0016641 oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors, oxygen as acceptor' (=EC:1.4.3.-)\",\n  \"comments\": [],\n  \"title\": \"GO:0052597 diamine oxidase activity terms\",\n  \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31964\"\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
